         <abstract id="aspace_091b2bc8f16ec342e66e92b9605727aa">Deeds and other legal documents, chiefly relating to land in Hamden, Connecticut owned by Ebenezer Warner and his sons, Amos and Ebenezer. Sixteen of the transfers are to Eldad Wolcott of Hamden.</abstract>
         <origination label="Creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part localtype="agent_person">Warner, Ebenezer, 1733-1811</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_ced1448c0a9e97d3332953d4568930f6">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Purchased in 1948.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_901eb51c6126785bc304ecc83393e5da">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_c108a528a91ff820dd3e841485f6db74">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Ebenezer Warner Family Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8b86e5a4226c5c3aab0c67678d9b6a2f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This small collection is made up entirely of deeds and other legal documents, 1775-1846, pertaining to members of the Warner family living in and around Hamden, Connecticut. The deeds, sixteen of which are to Eldad Wolcott of Hamden, refer primarily to the land belonging to Ebenezer Warner (1733-1811), to his son Ebenezer (1767-1855), and to Amos Warner. Also among the papers are several writs, summonses, and subpoenas. The papers are arranged chronologically.</p>
         <p>These documents were purchased for Yale University in 1948.</p>
      </scopecontent>
